title.narrative: PUBLIC FINANCE 4CHILDREN

description.narrative: By 2022, there is improved evidence, capacity and systems for equity sensitive planning, budgeting and implementation, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Reducing Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment, budgets and systems for all children, especially the most excluded, guided by improved knowledge and disaggregated data

title.narrative: By 2022, there is improved evidence, capacity and systems for equity sensitive planning, budgeting and implementation

description.narrative: Despite challenges posed by the third wave of COVID-19 pandemic and the military takeover since February 2021 that resulted in non-engagement with Ministry of Planning and Finance and other ministries on technical support and capacity building for Public Finance for Children, UNICEF continues to finalize the analysis and evidence-generation works on budget allocations to social sectors in FY 2020/2021 through a series of social sectors budget briefs analysis (Education, Health, Social Welfare and;Rural Water WASH). In addition, analysis of Myanmar public budget transparency and human capital investment initiatives for country’s public investment on children was completed. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
